sourcesContent: import Fashion from '../../image/Fashion.jpeg' import EditDelete from '../icons /EditDelete' import { SinglePost, SinglePostImage, SinglePostTitle, SinglePostInfo, Span, Name, SinglePostDescription, Introduction, } from './Singlepost.styled' import { imageStylePropsFashion } from './SinglePostStyle.styled' const SinglePostStyle = () => { return ( LookBook Author: Dohee Lee 2 hours ago First of all, I wish to express that I am a great admirer of Korean Fashion. I am wearing it myself every single day. Personally, i love purchasing korean clothes from either Shein and Yestyle. From tops to coats, and pants to dresses, I love wearing clothes oversized and they are especially a popular casual attire, existing even in the form of sweater dresses, and focused on utmost comfort. It also offers a cute but effortless look. I love to combine an oversized item with a tighter one, usually a loose t-shirt, blouse, or sweater, with a skirt. Others may wear an oversized top together with a loose bottom. In addition, i love wearing suits or blazers as it offers a professional look, which makes me look a lot smarter. These are popular types of style gaining popularity amongst Koreans. ) } export default SinglePostStyle
